<br>
Now I will talk about why human greed is actually a GOOD thing.  First let me point out that greed to me isn't the same as greed to everyone else, also a GOOD thing.  For example, one person may take absolute delight in making money off of someone else (in most cases this is fine, our judicial system takes care of the cases that aren't), another may find delight in helping others.  The second person covets feeling good about themselves for helping others.  You know what?  That's greed, and it's a damn good form of it.  These people exist and always will.  You will find them in classrooms, as social workers, youth counselors, etc.  Call it crazy but a lot of people in the world LIKE HELPING OTHER PEOPLE!  Maybe some of you don't but me personally, I take more joy in helping a kid get on the right track in life than downing X mob that I waited 8 hours for to spawn in a virtual world.  Not to say I don't enjoy both, but I will take the kid over the game any day.<br>
<br>
Human greed is also what created the automobile, the airplane, the microwave, and penicillin.  There was money and more importantly FAME to be gained out of coming up with these ideas.  As long as people want these two things, you will always see cutting edge innovations.  What this means is, there is money to be made off of figuring out how to grow plants in space, in how to fight global warming, in how to create water from nothing.  Greed my friends is for the most part a good thing.  Oh and before I forget, I am a Christian, a Mormon to be exact.  We believe that people have not only the God given right, but responsibility to raise as many children as they can sufficiently handle.  The key words being sufficiently handle.  That is, if I can feed, clothe, love, and ensure proper education for 10 kids (and my wife can handle having that many) then 10 kids it is!  Personally I only want 2-3 but that's me.  So you sit there probably thinking I am selfish, well you thought right I AM!  It's a darn good thing to, because look at it this way.  If I can raise 10 kids with a solid, loving upbringing and teach them to be productive members of society then my 10 kids can help support the two or three that didn't have an easy start in life.  Which means, you NEED my kids.  I can't, you can't, and no one else can completely keep everyone from having kids so if the ones that can produce well rounded ones produce more than those that shouldn't breed at all, we will be okay.  As for over population as a result...<br>
<br>
It won't happen.  Here is an analogy I thought up.  Say you have two identical plots of land and on each plot you place two groups of people.  Each plot in its current state can support 10 people 50 years or 100 people 5 years.  Plot A has 10 people and plot B 100 people.  Each person is expected to live 80 years.  It is possible to create more food on the land than the current yield permits and any method to increase that length of time is allowed.  So in 60 who do you think has the best chance to be alive?  You may say group A but history would be against you and sorry but you would probably end up dead after a little more than 50 years.  Plot B may only have 5 years to come up with something revolutionary but they have a better chance in 5 years than A does in 50.  The reason is manpower.  Take a look at the technology boom of this century.  In the ancient days (no well before your parent were born) technology doubled every few thousand years.  Around 1000 AD it was probably about every two hundred years, at the turn of the 20th century it was about 40-50 (total guess here) years and today it is less than 10.  In 10 years we will know twice as much as we do today.  If you don't believe me look it up.  I won't post a direct source since I can't think of one, try an Encyclopedia, its a pretty given fact amongst the egg-heads of the world.  Why?  The answer is people.  The more people there are then the more scientists we have and the more money and muscle we have to see their ideas take shape.  In essence, 100 people will come up with more ideas than 10 will.  If ever there comes a point where overpopulation starts to REALLY hurt, then rest assured that there will be plenty of people working on ways profitable to THEM to resolve it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utaeweil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taeweil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered 