     I would propse that the use of the term greed in a positive sense isn't really what I was referring to.  Yes, without a motivating force, most innovation would not have occurred.  I have to wonder though, did the Wright brothers fly for the money?  Or did they fly for the sake of flying, and the money was a secondary plus...  Did we go to the moon for money?  No... unfortunately we went to the moon solely to beat another country at doing the same thing.<br>
<br>
     Anyway, in reference to what you were speaking of.  It is the 'human nature' that must undergo a significant change.  The concept that one person must be more important than another is detrimental to society.  You speak as though our political system is working as itended.  I would say that it is not.  Any time decisions which may have a global impact are made based on religious beliefs, campaign funding, and corporate influence, the entire world is being done an injustice.  Do you think that George Bush could create a law that said that all corporations which discharged harmful chemicals will be shut down immediately?  Every last union worker from said companies would vote for 'the other guy' next time, every last cent that said corporations were donating to the campaign funds would go to 'the other guy'...  Its a sad system.<br>
<br>
     About population and Malthus' concepts.  You are not paying attention.  Yes, most 1st world nations utilize technologies which allow for greater food production density (but then again mabye not?  Hoof n' Mouth disease?  Mad cow?  etc..etc..).  What we DONT have are the nations that truely have food and water deficits utilizing this technology.  It is either cost prohibitive or there are other political/moral/religous reason for depriving these countries of said technology.<br>
<br>
     One more thing, once again to quote Sam Kinneson.  ITS SAND, NOTHING GROWS IN SAND.  Technology or not, there are many many areas of the globe which just *cannot* fully support the population which resides there currently.  Unfortunately, these are some of the places where the population grows the quickest...<br>
<br>
     Do I think that America and other 1st world countries will experience a population problem similar to that described by malthus?  No...  Not only do we have technology which allows us to create what we need to survive, but we are (generally) well educated, we (generally) have familys w/ 1.8 children or whatever today's magic number is, and we continue to develop new technologies which might help us in the future. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showMessageRange?topicID=446.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=446.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=446.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=446.topic&index=24><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=446.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.threadControl?topicID=446.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=446.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=446.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right